eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The National Coronavirus Command Council is set to meet soon and on the agenda: should tougher restrictions be imposed amid the third wave of COVID-19? Gauteng is leading the infection numbers but many are against tougher interventions, among them the Gauteng Education Department and South African Council of Churches. READ: Liquor industry warns against tougher restrictions Gauteng premier David Makhura has appealed to residents to continue observing regulations to help the province lower the rate of new infections. eNCA’s Lindokuhle Xulu shares more details in the video above.